    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public IPrimitiveController getInstance(java.lang.String className)
        Gets an instance a IPrimitiveController based on the provided className parameter. On first request, the class is resolved, an instance is created and the IPrimitiveController.initController method is called to initialise the controller. For resolution to succeed:
        1. The provide className is a fully qualified class name or be a class resident in one of the configured packages.
        2. The class must implement the IPrimitiveController interface
        4. The initController method must succeed, that is return true.
        Parameters:
        className - class to get an instance of
        Returns:
        instance or null if the name cannot be resolved
